<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="partner_template/macros/page"
      i18n:domain="cc_org">
  <head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Choose a License</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="body"
         tal:define="target_lang string:en;
                     stylesheet request_form/stylesheet | nothing;
                     exiturl    request_form/exit_url | string:'';
                     pd_exiturl python:exiturl.replace('&', '%26');
                     partner    request_form/partner | nothing;
                     partner_icon_url python: request_form.get('partner_icon_url','/images/remote_logo.gif');
                     show_jurisdiction request_form/jurisdiction_chooser | nothing;
                     def_juris request_form/jurisdiction | nothing;">

      <h1 i18n:translate="license.confirm_choice">Confirm Choice</h1>

      <p i18n:translate="license.zero.intro_1">
	  Using CC0, you can waive all copyrights and related or
	  neighboring rights that you have over your work, such as
	  your moral rights (to the extent waivable), your publicity
	  or privacy rights, rights you have protecting against unfair
	  competition, and database rights and rights protecting the
	  extraction, dissemination and reuse of data.
      </p>

      <p i18n:translate="license.zero.intro_2">
	  Keep in mind that you cannot waive rights to a work that you
	  do not own unless you have permission from the owner.  To
	  avoid infringing third party rights, you should consult with
	  your legal advisor if you are unsure whether you have all
	  the rights you need to distribute the work.
      </p>

      <p i18n:translate="license.partner.zero.use_pdm_instead">
        If instead you want to certify that a work is
        <em>already in the public domain</em>, use the
        <span tal:omit-tag="" i18n:name="pd_url"
              tal:content="string:/choose/mark/partner?lang=${target_lang}&partner=${partner}&exit_url=${pd_exiturl}&license_code=publicdomain&stylesheet=${stylesheet}" />
        <a href="${pd_url}">Public Domain Mark</a>.
      </p>

      <p i18n:translate="license.you_may_proceed">
        <span tal:omit-tag=""
              i18n:name="processed_exit_url" tal:content="exit_url" />
You may now <a href="#" tal:attributes="href exit_url">proceed</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
